 Adapter Pattern in .NET Core
The Adapter Pattern is a structural design pattern that allows incompatible interfaces to work together.

It acts as a bridge between an existing class and a required interface without modifying either.

“The Adapter Pattern converts the interface of a class into another interface that clients expect.”

 Real‑World Analogy

Mobile charger adapter

Phone expects 5V USB
Wall socket gives 230V AC
Adapter converts one interface to another



➡️ Same idea in software

The Problem It Solves
You have:

Existing / third‑party / legacy code
Interface mismatch
You cannot change the existing code

But:

Your system expects a different interface


✅ Solution: Adapter Pattern
Wrap the incompatible class with an adapter that translates calls.

